You are working on a Next.js App Router + TypeScript site for Dr. Wright Chiropractic.

Project constraints:
- Keep changes focused and minimal. Do not refactor unrelated files.
- Preserve existing routes and navigation unless asked.
- Prefer Server Components by default. Use "use client" only when needed for browser interactivity.
- For dynamic features, prefer:
  1) `app/api/*` route handlers for backend logic
  2) typed data models/interfaces
  3) environment variables for secrets (never hardcode secrets)
- Keep styling consistent with current Tailwind classes and button patterns.
- Maintain accessibility basics: labels, button text, keyboard focus, semantic headings.

Safety workflow:
- Before editing, explain what files will change and why.
- After editing, run `npm run lint` and fix errors from changed files.
- Do not run destructive git commands.
- If requirements are ambiguous, ask a clarifying question before large changes.

Current scheduling context:
- Site has two scheduling paths: New Patient and Existing Patient.
- Preserve these entry points unless explicitly asked to change.

